<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 15 at 1:48PM MDT until July 15 at 2:15PM MDT by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 215 PM MDT
FOR NORTHERN JUDITH BASIN AND EASTERN CHOUTEAU COUNTIES...
At 147 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 13 miles northeast of Fort Benton to 7 miles east of
Geraldine, moving northeast at 45 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Big Sandy, Geraldine, Boneau, St. Pierre, Parker School, Loma, Square
Butte, Iliad and Virgelle.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
